MHD_digest_auth_calc_userhash calls strlen(username) and strlen(realm) without validating that the pointers are non-NULL and point to NUL-terminated arrays. If a caller passes username == NULL or realm == NULL (or a pointer to a non NUL-terminated buffer), strlen will read past the object bounds (undefined behavior). For example, calling MHD_digest_auth_calc_userhash(algo, NULL, "realm", ...) or passing a realm buffer missing a terminating '\0' will cause strlen to access beyond the object.
